Let $P$ be the principal you invested four years ago.  After four years, at 10% annual interest compounded yearly, the account will have grown to $1.10^4 P = 1.4641P$.  Therefore we must solve the equation
\[1.4641P = 439.23.\]Dividing both sides by $1.4641$, we find $P = \boxed{300}$.
